The paper discusses quality control in crowdsourcing, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY). It also involves social and information sciences (cs.SI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR) as the paper discusses tasks such as labeling images, translating or transcribing text, and providing opinions or ideas.
